Phacelia hastata
Filtering workflow & exploration of parameters

Initially filtering on 3 things:

  • SNPs only (no indels) --remove-indels
  • biallelic sites only --min-alleles 2 and --max-alleles 2
  • 1 SNP per contig (helps account for LD, our reads are typically <100 BP length) --thin 100
  • OPTIONAL (but I typically do) - filter on call quality. Our call qualities are typically very good so it doesnt get rid of much but might as well cut out the worst stuff --minQ 30
vcftools \
--gzvcf PHHA.vcf.gz \
--remove-indels \
--min-alleles 2 \
--max-alleles 2 \
--thin 100 \
--minQ 30 \
--remove-filtered-all \
--recode \
--recode-INFO-all \
--out PHHA.bithin.q30

Produces file PHHA.bithin.q30.recode.vcf

Making a summary file to look at individual missingness

vcftools \
--vcf PHHA.bithin.q30.recode.vcf \
--missing-indv \
--out PHHA.bithin.q30

Produces file called PHHA.bithin.q30.imiss
